# =========================================
# WARLOCK: ARCHFEY PATRON FEATURES
# =========================================

"Archfey Patron: Patron Spells":
  title: "Archfey Patron Level 3: Patron Spells"
  desc: "The magic of your otherworldly patron ensures you always have certain spells ready; when you reach a Warlock level specified in the Archfey Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared."
  fields:
  - title: "Archfey Spells Table"
    body: "```\n| Warlock | Prepared\n|  Level  | Spells\n|---------+-----------------------------------------------------------------\n|    3    | Calm Emotions, Faerie Fire, Misty Step, Phantasmal Force, Sleep\n|    5    | Blink, Plant Growth\n|    7    | Dominate Beast, Greater Invisibility\n|    9    | Dominate Person, Seeming\n\n```"
  - body: "[Packet 7](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-7)"

"Archfey Patron: Steps of the Fey":
  title: "Archfey Patron Level 3: Steps of the Fey"
  desc: "Your patron bestows on you the ability to move between the boundaries of the planes. You can cast _Misty Step_ without expending a spell slot a number of times equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest.\n\nIn addition, whenever you cast that spell, you can choose one of the following additional effects.\n\n**Refreshing Step**. Immediately after you teleport, one creature you can see within 10 feet of you gains 1d10 Temporary Hit Points.\n\n**Taunting Step**. Creatures within 5 feet of the space you left must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw against your spell save DC or have Disadvantage on attack rolls against creatures other than you until the start of your next turn."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 7](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-7)"

"Archfey Patron: Misty Escape":
  title: "Archfey Patron Level 6: Misty Escape"
  desc: "You can vanish in a puff of mist in response to harm. You can cast _Misty Step_ as a Reaction in response to taking damage.\n\nIn addition, the following effects are now among your Steps of the Fey options.\n\n**Disappearing Step**. You have the Invisible condition until the start of your next turn or until immediately after you make an attack roll or cast a spell.\n\n**Dreadful Step**. Creatures within 5 feet of the space you left or the space you appear in (your choice) must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw against your spell save DC or take 2d10 Psychic damage."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 7](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-7)"

"Archfey Patron: Beguiling Defenses":
  title: "Archfey Patron Level 10: Beguiling Defenses"
  desc: "Your patron teaches you how to guard your mind and body. You are immune to the Charmed condition.\n\nIn addition, immediately after a creature you can see hits you with an attack roll, you can use your Reaction to reduce the damage you take by half (round down), and you can force the attacker to make a Wisdom saving throw against your spell save DC. On a failed save, the attacker takes Psychic damage equal to the damage you take.\n\nOnce you use this Reaction, you can't use it again until you finish a Long Rest unless you expend a spell slot when you use it again."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 7](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-7)"

"Archfey Patron: Bewitching Magic":
  title: "Archfey Patron Level 14: Bewitching Magic"
  desc: "Your patron bestows on you the ability to weave your magic with teleportation. Immediately after you cast an Enchantment or Illusion spell using an action and a spell slot, you can cast _Misty Step_ as part of the same action and without expending a spell slot."
  fields:
  - body: "[Packet 7](https://www.dndbeyond.com/sources/ua/ph-playtest-7)"


